title: Turkey Reserve Requirement Ratio Foreign Currency
description: Cash Reserve Ratio in Turkey remained unchanged at 25 percent in October from 25 percent in September of 2022. Cash Reserve Ratio in Turkey averaged 12.77 percent from 2002 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 25 percent in October of 2021 and a record low of 9 percent in November of 2008. This page provides - Turkey Cash Reserve Ratio- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of the Republic of Turkey
